      <ul>
        <li><strong style="color:#e8eaed">Weekly OB:</strong> Defines the macro directional bias. Sweeps of weekly OBs launch multi-week trends. Rarely retested but extremely powerful when they are.</li>
        <li><strong style="color:#e8eaed">Daily OB:</strong> Sets the weekly range. Intraday price often retraces to test daily OBs during London or NY sessions before continuing the trend.</li>
        <li><strong style="color:#e8eaed">4H OB:</strong> The workhouse timeframe for swing traders. 4H OBs within daily structure provide excellent risk/reward with manageable stops.</li>
        <li><strong style="color:#e8eaed">1H OB:</strong> Refined entry zones for intraday trades. Use 1H OBs for timing entries after a 4H or Daily OB is confirmed as support/resistance.</li>
        <li><strong style="color:#e8eaed">15M / 5M OB:</strong> Precision entry refinement. Drop to M15 to find the specific OB within the HTF zone for the tightest possible stop.</li>
